description:
&lt;p&gt;An exciting opportunity has arisen for a Medical Secretary to join the Knowsley Mental Health Services based in Knowsley Resource and Recovery Centre, Whiston Hospital Site, L35 5DR.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Working as part of the administration team, you will provide a full Medical Secretarial role, audio typing, dictation and administrative support to the department&#39;s Medical Team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The hours of work will be over 3 to 5 days from Monday to Friday 9am to 5pm (pro rata 22.5hrs).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will need to have:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• Excellent oral and written communication skills&lt;br /&gt;• Knowledge of arranging meetings and taking minutes&lt;br /&gt;• Strong organisational skills&lt;br /&gt;• Thorough attention to detail and high standards of accuracy&lt;br /&gt;• A flexible attitude and ability to work as part of a team&lt;br /&gt;• RSA/OCR Stage III typing/audio typing/word processing or equivalent. &lt;br /&gt;• Previous audio typing and extensive word processing knowledge. &lt;br /&gt;• Skilled in typing and preparing reports for Tribunals and Managers’ hearings, letters to GPs and other Professionals where deemed appropriate &lt;br /&gt;• Experience of diary Management and excellent IT skills&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This post is subject to a standard Disclosure and Barring Service (DBS) Check. Successful candidates will either have a valid DBS check with the Trust or will be required to pay for the cost of the DBS Disclosure which is and £29.50 for a standard disclosure, the cost of which will be deducted from first salary.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Jennie Beckwith - Admin Service Manager&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Jennie.Beckwith@NWBH.nhs.uk / 0151 290 4999&lt;/p&gt;
